        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[<p>My friend Adam was telling me about <a href="https://www.worldcommunitygrid.org">World Community Grid</a> the other day, which is a program for performing distributed research projects by allowing anyone to donate otherwise unused computing power to the program.  It reminds me of <a href="https://distributed.net">distributed.net</a>, with arguably nobler causes behind the project.  I have a good chunk of unused cpu and gpu capacity laying around so I decided I&rsquo;d set up the <a href="https://boinc.berkeley.edu/">boinc client</a> on my homelab.</p>
<p>Boinc is essentially a client program that enrolls your computer as a worker in a project like World Community Grid and coordinates the work on your system.</p>]]></summary>
